<font color="#FF0000">WHAT A WASTE OF TIME 'N ENERGY</font><br>
<tt>Thu May  1  3:29:05 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
When you dissect a frog, you kill it in the process. It is destroyed, gone. Sometimes there are things best left alone. The writings I posted are a good case in point. Just allow those who read it to take whatever they walk away with. I know why I left them on the site, but someone else may get something else out of them. What does it matter?<br><br>
About the other matter, Betty, the things that you mentioned, you know, god, buddhism, two wrongs...., that kind of stuff does not mean anything to me as I believe it to be all garbage. So, your point is moot. I believe in other things that you have not touched on, but they are inconsequential. I have done nothing wrong. If you go back to Barry's beginning on site, you see that he really over reacts to situations, reads things that are not there, whatever, and then he does a number like yelling, ranting, and raving. In the process he stirs up a fellow or two until he runs out of steam or some others beats him over the head a few times. This cycle has played itself out a few times already, i.e., the case of the monster feminist; Kali Tal. He approaches her to try to get funding for this site, royally insults the women by telling how bad her site is and how good this one is. Then he asks for support. What do you think her reaction was? When she shows a little defensiveness, what happens, but the infamous e-mail on the site, a thread dedicated for agressive and hostile remarks, personal, and professional attacks. And what else? Finally one or two voices of reason, (not me)slaps him in the head publicly, which in turn humiliates the &quot;troops&quot; and the whole thing falls apart.  I have seen Kali Tal's post up for at least a couple of days and what, nothing. Because there was nothing in his hysteria in the first place but blatant bravado.<br><br>
With my post, he again, as well as his troops, are overreacting. You folks are wasting time and cyberspace on this issue. I stand by my original post. Move on, you're wasting daylight!
